    "summary": "www.yasserballemans.nl\n\nSpecialties: Fine Art\n\nHow to collectively imagine, plan and create an inclusive, sustainable and righteous future? As a visual artist, Yasser Ballemans is interested in the role of art in rituals, such as parades, campfires, carnival and commemorations. He researches how ornaments, decorations and \u201cold-fashioned\u201d techniques can be used in a contemporary way.\u00a0Collective artistic practices play a major role in his ongoing research into the role of art in the much needed social and political innovations.\n\nYasser Ballemans (Breda 1981) received his bachelor's degree in visual arts from the art academy AKV / St. Joost (Breda), graduated in 2007 (MA visual arts) from the Sandberg Institute (Amsterdam) and followed the Mr Miyagi Curators Master Class of Showroom MAMA in Rotterdam in 2005.\n\nMonumental sculptures in public space are located in Rotterdam, Amsterdam, Nieuwegein, Utrecht and the Arnhem Palace of Justice, among others.\u00a0Ballemans has had several solo exhibitions, including Museum de Fundatie (Heino), Onomatopee (Eindhoven), Park (Tilburg) and Gallery Joey Ramone (Rotterdam). In addition, his work has been shown in group exhibitions in China, Cura\u00e7ao, England, France and South Korea. In the Netherlands he took part in group exhibitions at Beeldhalwerk, Stedelijk Museum Bureau Amsterdam, W139 and the Africa Museum.\n\nIn addition to his work as a visual artist, Ballemans was a curator, entrepreneur, teacher and producer in the art world. He was involved as an advisor at TENT, was part of the\u00a0Council for Culture in the Assessment Committee BIS 2021 - 2024, worked as\u00a0a curator at Kunstvlaai, was one of the founders of the experimental exhibition space KOP in Breda and he was involved in the work of artist Jeanne van Heeswijk for several years. Among others as curator at the Blue House and as producer for Freehouse and Face Your World.\u00a0For\u00a0Kunstpodium T\u00a0Ballemans is Yearmaster of the Apprentice Master project in the 2021/2022 season. Ballemans teaches at the Education (BA) and the\u00a0Crossover Creativity (MA)\u00a0department at the HKU.\n\nSince 2023, Yasser Ballemans has been the initiator of the restart of the Kunstvlaai; a manifestation of experimental art stages. In his contemporary work, Ballemans explores ways to create platforms for interactive, collective and interdisciplinary creativity.\n\nYasser Ballemans lives and works in Amsterdam.",
