                    "company": "Kunstvlaai",
                    "description": "Kunstvlaai, known as a platform for experimental art spaces, will be renewed in 2023. Commissioned by Stichting Kunstvlaai, the coming months artist and organizer Yasser Ballemans will work on a new vision for the future. \n \nAccording to Ballemans, artist-run project spaces and other collective artistic practices are very suitable to experiment with the role art can play in society. He will further develop Kunstvlaai into a platform with a focus on collective artistic practices with an emphasis on common interests. The future Kunstvlaai will bring these collectives together, make them co-owners and challenge them to create new artistic forms of presentation and develop new ideas. It will also be a place in which ideas about collectivity can be shared, discussed and developed. Concrete plans and projects are expected in the second half of 2023. Are you interested in the plans and would you like to contact us? Send an email to info@kunsvlaai.nl.\n\nYasser Ballemans\nYasser Ballemans (Breda 1981) obtained his bachelor's degree as a visual artist at the art academy AKV/St. Joost and his master at the Sandberg Institute. He also attended Showroom MAMA's Mr Miyagi Curators Master Class. In addition to his work as an artist, he is a curator, teacher, consultant and producer in the art world. He was involved in various roles in various organizations such as the Council for Culture, TENT, Kunstvlaai, KOP and the work of artist Jeanne van Heeswijk. Ballemans teaches at the Education (BA) and Crossover Creativity (MA) departments of the HKU. In his work he explores ways to create platforms for interactive, collective and interdisciplinary creativity. Yasser lives and works in Amsterdam.\n\nFor more information, see www.kunstvlaai.nl",
                    "title": "Transition Kunstvlaai",
